
=Bio=

'''Jaap W.J. baron van Till''' (61) is an electronic networks engineer who has experience in the telecom, computer network and Internet-infrastructure fields, and is working at the cutting edge of new disruptive technologies and emerging peer-to- peer community tools.

He learned from his projects as a “Network Architect" in the corporate and factory networks of Akzo Nobel all over Europe. Later he helped to design large corporate computer networks for businesses, government ministries and the NL NREN (national research and education network) SURFnet. 

Jaap van Till is senior partner at Statix Consulting and professor at the HAN university in Arnhem (NL). He was professor at the Delft University (NL) and the University of Kaunas (Lithuania) and frequently teaches at business schools, like the Institut Theseus in Nice (France).

Jaap dot vantill AT han dot nl
Essay about p2p upstreamers is at  http://www.vantill.dds.nl/p2pupstreamers.html

